root: ^“I barely know who you are now and the very sight of you shame me.”
^“You, with all that numbness and emptiness and nothingness.”
^“How could you be just so dull?”
^“You go on, living on that dull life of yours but don’t you dare to strip what I have away from me.”
^“Ohhh poor boy trying to fight back? Adorable! But what a pity you have nothing to fight back with!”
^“You really think that would get me?”
^“Oh I see you opening your mouth but you can’t squeeze a sound out of that throat of you?”
^“That useless, mechanical, boring, boring throat of you.”
^“Trying to tear me down with that nothingness? ”
^“Making me live a boring life like you are now?”
^“I protect what I have, unlike you who have exactly nothing.”
^“If I’m kinder I might teach you what love[insert any attack ability name] is, would you like that?”
^“And I bet you don’t know what [insert any attack ability name] is, my fledgling.”
^“Or am I the fledgling of you, my empty-hearted, self-absorbing, always the “I’ve got work to do, master?”
